body: See: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/9568. We may need to add back the .targets files.

Yes, generating this file is exactly what the `install(EXPORT)` command that was removed in #9568 does. Without it, the other CMake package stuff is entirely useless.

However, if you just add it back in, #8729 is still going to be an issue for anyone using the in-tree versions of protobuf, c-ares, zlib and ssl (unless those in-tree versions install their own CMake package files, which protobuf might, but c-ares definitely doesn't).

My suggestion would be to only enable the CMake package code (both `install(EXPORT)` and the `gRPCConfig.cmake`/`gRPCConfigVersion.cmake` stuff at the end of `CMakeLists.txt`) if those four dependencies are set to "package" mode. Note that #11006 is kind of related to this as well.

> However, if you just add it back in, #8729 is still going to be an issue for anyone using the in-tree versions of protobuf, c-ares, zlib and ssl (unless those in-tree versions install their own CMake package files, which protobuf might, but c-ares definitely doesn't).

Why these users just not set `gRPC_INSTALL=OFF`? I've added `gRPC_INSTALL` specially for that
That's also an option. But the error messages if the user fails to do that are not helpful. Something that checked for the wrong combination of settings and gave a more useful error might be good.

> My suggestion would be to only enable the CMake package code (both install(EXPORT) and the gRPCConfig.cmake/gRPCConfigVersion.cmake stuff at the end of CMakeLists.txt) if those four dependencies are set to "package" mode.

Agree with you, we should set gRPC_INSTALL=OFF when one of the packages are set to "module" mode and revert c019e057c20db0b9c9a2f76fb0b9cd6f44addf92

I am having trouble cmake-ing the cpp helloworld example on windows, because of this issue. Cmake Configure step fails with: 
```
CMake Error at C:/dev/grpc/.build/gRPCConfig.cmake:8 (include):
  include could not find load file:

    C:/dev/grpc/.build/gRPCTargets.cmake

Call Stack (most recent call first):
  CMakeLists.txt:13 (find_package)
```

I am using Protobuf 3.4.1 and gRPC 1.6.2. 
Based on the conversation above I have tried rebuilding gRPC with gRPC_INSTALL=FALSE, but it has no effect.

Any suggestions?

First compiled protobuf from within grpc.
Then attempted to compile grpc with command
```
cmake .. -DgRPC_INSTALL=OFF
```
And still received:

```
 include could not find load file:             
                                               
   /usr/local/lib/cmake/grpc/gRPCTargets.cmake 
```

I searched my whole system for it and couldn't find the generated file so it not a prefix issue. There must be something simple I'm missing.

As a sanity check I commented out
```
if  (gRPC_INSTALL)
```
On line 14773 of CMakeLists.txt and arrived at the same outcome.
